title.narrative: Amount of economic & financial crime Assets recovered by EFCC
Number of pilot restructuring plans fully implemented

comment.narrative: All four pilot civil service agencies designed restructuring plans at the start of the project and began restructuring theiroperations, but this continues to evolve in response to changing priorities in government.

title.narrative: Percentage of large government contract awards published.

comment.narrative: All large government contracts are published on the website of the Bureau of Public Procurement.

title.narrative: Number of agencies with budget and financial reports prepared from GIFMIS within 7 days of month's end.

comment.narrative: The budget execution sub-system of GIFMIS went live in April 2012 with 93 MDAs now executing their transactions via the GIFMIS TSAsystem. 116 more MDAs have recently been added on the BES-TSA system by end-April 2012.

title.narrative: Percentage of professional staff who have received training in their areas.
Percentage of NBS statistical outputs released within the GDDS time and frequency limits.
Percentage of NBS staff with requisite professional background and skills

comment.narrative: This percentage is set to improve significantly as the NBS has almost concluded the recruitment of a large set of statisticiansandanalysts.

title.narrative: Backlog of Audited Financial Statements of the Federal Government

comment.narrative: All backlogs have been cleared and the Office of the Auditor-General now prepares the audit reports within the stipulated timelines.

title.narrative: Percentage of professional staff in pilot ministries.

comment.narrative: The PCU is in the process of hiring a consultant to work with the relevant agencies to measure this indicator.

title.narrative: Percentage of data sources, processing methods and statistical products that are validated
Effective procurement regulatory body established (defined as effectively enforcing the procurement bill and implementing regulations and providing guidance for procurement capacity in the MDAs)

comment.narrative: The Bureau of Public Procurement (BPP) is Nigeria's Procurement regulatory Body which was established following the enactment ofthe Federal Public Procurement Law in 2007.

title.narrative: Number of economic & financial crime prosecutions by EFCC.

comment.narrative: This is from revised data supplied by the EFCC
